The paper deals with algorithms for graph representations of genomes, which suggests that it falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The use of directed acyclic graphs (DAGs) in the paper also suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of computational geometry (cs.CG) or graph theory (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the minimum path cover problem, which is a classic problem in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and the use of dynamic programming algorithms, which is a common technique in scientific computing (cs.SC).
